      • loadContent

        public void loadContent(ContentManager content)
        Description copied from interface: IGameDelegate
        Loads content such as image and sounds files and other data into the game. The GameActivty will call this once right before entering the game engine enters the game loop. The ShipBuilding activity calls this function in its onCreate() function.
        Specified by:
        loadContent in interface IGameDelegate
        Parameters:
        content - An instance of the content manager. This should be used to load images and sound files.

      • unloadContent

        public void unloadContent(ContentManager content)
        Description copied from interface: IGameDelegate
        Unloads content from the game. The GameActivity will call this function after the game engine exits the game loop. The ShipBuildingActivity will call this function after the "Start Game" button has been pressed.
        Specified by:
        unloadContent in interface IGameDelegate
        Parameters:
        content - An instance of the content manager. This should be used to unload image and sound files.

      • update

        public void update(double elapsedTime)
        Description copied from interface: IGameDelegate
        Updates the game delegate. The game engine will call this function 60 times a second once it enters the game loop.
        Specified by:
        update in interface IGameDelegate
        Parameters:
        elapsedTime - Time since the last update. For this game, elapsedTime is always 1/60th of second
